    "description": "Metro Cash & Carry Capital India invites applications from qualified candidates for the position of Department Manager at our Bengaluru location. This role offers excellent career advancement prospects.\n\nAbout Metro Cash & Carry Capital India:\nMetro Cash & Carry Capital India is a leading organization in the Hybrid sector, committed to excellence, innovation, and employee growth. We offer a dynamic work environment where talent is recognized and rewarded.\n\nKey Responsibilities:\n• Coordinate with the supply chain team for timely stock delivery\n• Train and motivate the sales team to deliver excellent service\n• Handle customer queries, complaints, and escalations effectively\n• Implement promotional activities and in-store campaigns\n• Assist in recruiting, onboarding, and performance management of staff\n• Maintain high standards of store hygiene and cleanliness\n• Monitor inventory levels and coordinate replenishment activities\n\nRequired Skills & Qualifications:\n• Any graduate with relevant experience\n• 6-10 years of relevant experience\n• Proficiency in Loss Prevention\n• Proficiency in KPI Management\n• Proficiency in SAP Retail\n• Proficiency in Shrinkage Control\n• Proficiency in Omnichannel Retail\n• Proficiency in Team Leadership\n• Proficiency in POS Systems\n• Proficiency in Visual Merchandising\n\nWork Mode: Hybrid - Flexible work-from-home and office\n\nWhat We Offer:\n• Work-from-home flexibility\n• Annual paid leaves and casual leaves\n• Mobile and internet reimbursement\n• Maternity and paternity leave\n• Modern office with recreational facilities\n• Recognition and rewards programs\n• Salary Range: 12 LPA - 25 LPA per annum\n\nLocation: Bengaluru, Karnataka, India\n\nIf you are excited about this opportunity, apply now and take the next step in your career journey with Metro Cash & Carry Capital India!",
